Hi Hacker News,
I would like to suggest you trying out our application Actisto.com, which was developed by our team.
Here are main features:<p>It is free web application for free online calling, files & screen sharing;
It does not require any registration, or installation, you need only internet connection and web browser, which supports WebRTC technology (we suggest Chrome);
Secured transfer of data via SSL encryption;
We offer option to build-in Actisto icon (widget) into any website for faster connection.

I don&#x27;t see how this is a language killer feature. It looks more like a library feature. And yes, Perl 6 has a superb unicode library. In other languages, you can add the functionality as libraries. This is an example in Python:<p><pre><code>    import unicodedata

    def count_graphemes(string):
        count = 0
        for codepoint in string:
            if not unicodedata.category(codepoint).startswith(&#x27;M&#x27;):
                count += 1
        return count

    print(count_graphemes(&quot;ปฏิบัติจริง&quot;)) # prints 7
</code></pre>
This example is over simplified as grapheme clusters are trickier to detect, but proper support is coming to Python&#x27;s standard library: <a href="http://bugs.python.org/issue18406" rel="nofollow">http://bugs.python.org/issue18406</a>

It&#x27;s a bit messy, but:<p><pre><code>    js.eval(&#x27;var div = document.createElement(&quot;div&quot;); div.style.width = &quot;100px&quot;; div.style.height = &quot;100px&quot;; div.style.background = &quot;red&quot;; div.style.color = &quot;white&quot;; div.innerHTML = &quot;Hello&quot;; document.body.appendChild(div);&#x27;);
</code></pre>
manages to append a div.<p>--<p>Directly modifying document.body.innerHTML in any way seems to hang it. Both:<p><pre><code>    js.eval(&#x27;document.body.innerHTML += &quot;<div></div>&quot;;&#x27;);
    js.globals.document.body.innerHTML += &quot;<div></div>&quot;
</code></pre>
Cause it to hang, though the javascript console shows it was added (or using an img tag instead).<p>(ChromeOS v43 beta)
